	<h1>Review Trades</h1>
	<p class="tagline">Analyze closed positions with screenshots and statistics.</p>

	<img src="/docs/prismchart/thinkpad/ThinkPad-20260126-6.jpg" alt="ThinkPad Trade Analysis View" />

	<h2 id="trade-analysis-view">Trade Analysis View</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Review everything about a completed trade in one place.</p>

	<p>Click the Trades Manager button and find your closed trade. Click on the main trade row (not the partial exits underneath) and click View in the bottom right.</p>

	<p>The Trade Analysis window opens with your screenshot viewer on the left, a thumbnail strip below for navigation, and complete trade statistics on the right. Your note named "main" appears here. If you edit via Trade Analysis View, a "main" note is automatically created.</p>

	<h2 id="trade-statistics">Trade Statistics</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Understand your execution and results.</p>

	<p>The right panel shows position details including direction, volume, entry/exit times, and exact duration. The P/L breakdown lists gross profit, commission, swap fees, net profit, and final balance.</p>

	<p>Green indicates profit, red indicates losses and costs. Use this to verify execution quality, calculate actual risk/reward, review holding time versus your plan, and document costs for tax records.</p>

	<h2 id="editing-notes-post-trade">Editing Notes Post-Trade</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Add your review while statistics are fresh.</p>

	<p>Scroll down in the right panel to see your main note. Click in the note area to edit and add your post-trade review - what worked, what didn't, lessons learned.</p>

	<p>Click Save Note when done, or click Edit in ThinkPad for extensive changes in the full editor.</p>

	<h2 id="adding-screenshots-later">Adding Screenshots Later</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Attach images you captured after the fact.</p>

	<p>In Trade Analysis view, click Add Image and browse to your screenshot. It's added as the last in sequence - use Reorder if you need it elsewhere.</p>

	<p class="note">Add screenshots of final results, equity curve snapshots, or key levels hit for future reference.</p>
</DocsLayout>
